== Description ==

Your Wordpress admin menu is a mess? This is the perfect plugin for you! With this plugin you can reorder, hide and rename items in the Admin Menu as easy as pie!

1. Drag and Drop the items of your Menu in the correct order.

2. Rename the items.

3. Click "hide" in the items you want to hide.

4. Press save.

*Important* If you hide the settings item, you will not able to modify the items again. You'll have to deactivate the plugin.

Do you use worpdress admin with an iPad? DonÂ´t worry, this plugin is fully adapted for tablets and smartphones.

*Thank you for downloading! your feedback is well appreciated!*

== Installation ==

This section describes how to install the plugin and get it working.

1. Upload plugin folder `easy-admin-menu` to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory
2. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress

== Frequently Asked Questions ==

= Where do I specify the order? =

Go to Settings -> Easy Admin Menu page in your Admin Panel.

= The "Easy Admin Menu" Options page looks weird =

Clear your browser cache, the styling may change between versions.

